								<td valign="top" class="bodytext" style="width: 2495px">    
								<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">    
								<b><br />    
								</b>    
                                </font>
                                <p class="MsoNormal">
                                <span style="mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt">Avant is      
                                always looking for experienced structured      
                                cabling technicians.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;      
                                </span>If you would like to be considered for      
                                current or future opportunities, and meet the      
                                below listed requirements, submit your resume      
                                and salary requirements to </span><a href="mailto:resumes@avantdata.com"><font color="#0000FF"><u><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt">R</span></u></font><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt"><font color="#0000FF"><u>esumes@Avantdata.com</u></font></span></a><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:    
11.0pt">.<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                </span><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt"></o:p>    
                                </span></p>    
                                <p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="font-variant:small-caps;color:#003333">Position     
                                Summary:<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                <br>    
                                </span></u></b><span style="color:#003333;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold">Under     
                                the direct supervision, performs voice and/or     
                                data cable installation duties.</span> <b><span style="color:#003333"><o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                </span></b></p>    
                                <p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="font-variant:small-caps;color:#003333">Responsibilities:</span></u></b><br>    
                                Perform all cable pulling and installation     
                                processes.<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                </p>    
                                <ul type="disc">    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Terminate, label and test a     
                                    variety of different manufactures     
                                    connectivity hardware. (ie: jacks, patch     
                                    panels, 110 blocks, 66 blocks, RG6, RG11,     
                                    Splitters)<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Construction of communication     
                                    closets. (i.e.: equipment racks, ladder     
                                    rack, trough, shelving, cabinets).<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Installation of cable pathway     
                                    development, raceway and attachments.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Perform fiber optic cable     
                                    terminations and testing. <o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                </ul>    
                                <p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="font-variant:small-caps;color:#003333">Minimum     
                                Requirements:<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                <br>    
                                </span></u></b>High School Diploma/GED and 2 to     
                                5 years’ experience with the proper pulling     
                                techniques for all category cable, coaxial     
                                cable, fiber optic cable and high pair count     
                                copper backbone cabling.<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                </p>    
                                <ul type="disc">    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Ability to fully interpret and     
                                    work from project drawings. <o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Familiar with a variety of AV     
                                    cabling terminations, (RGB, VGA, RCA),     
                                    Security cabling techniques, (door frames,     
                                    cameras), Security cabling terminations,     
                                    (BNC, wire terminals).<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Strong understanding of proper     
                                    attachment hardware, mounting procedures and     
                                    raceway construction. (i.e.: Panduit,     
                                    Wiremold). <o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Solid understanding of cabling     
                                    standards (ANSI/TIA/EIA 568B, BICSI, NEC,     
                                    IEEE, NFPA).<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;     
                                    </span><o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Valid driver’s license and     
                                    insurance.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Ability to successfully pass a     
                                    background check and drug screen.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Ability to work flexible     
                                    hours, i.e., weekends or late afternoons and     
                                    evenings.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Cannot be colorblind.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Must be able to provide your     
                                    own basic working toolkit.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">Must be able to routinely lift     
                                    and carry up to 50 lbs. <o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                </ul>    
                                <p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="font-variant:small-caps;color:#003333">Minimum     
                                Education Requirements:<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                <br>    
                                </span></u></b>High School Diploma/GED and 2 to     
                                5 years’ experience with the proper pulling     
                                techniques for all category cable, coaxial     
                                cable, fiber optic cable and high pair count     
                                copper backbone cabling.<o:p>    
                                </o:p>    
                                </p>    
                                <ul type="disc">    
                                  <li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;    
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in">7 years’ directly related     
                                    experience can be substituted for a High     
                                    School diploma.<o:p>    
                                    </o:p>    
                                  </li>    
                                </ul>    
                                <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt"><o:p>    
                                &nbsp;</o:p>   
